  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The `/validator/duites` HTTP endpoint always skips to the first slot of the requested `epoch`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/78d82d9193ded34948433a73a56cf06dc9119812/beacon_node/rest_api/src/validator.rs#L96-L100\r\n\r\nIf the requested `epoch` is either the previous, current or next epoch of the head state, then there is no need to do any skipping/state loading. This is likely to be the case the majority of the time.\r\n\r\n### To resolve\r\n\r\nJust use the `beacon_chain.head()` state if it is in either the previous, next or current epoch of the request `epoch`. ",
